<br>
but is str valuable for melees. hell ya its valuable.  its funny ive seen people in one post brag how valuable avatar was to damage production then tell someone else how useless str is.  HELLO.  ATTACK IS ATTACK and it MATTERS.<br>
<br>
So thats STR.  then there is STA 100 sta gets you to no fatigue via low bar.  every STA at level 60 gets you 4 hp. hp is valuable.<br>
<br>
So thats STR and STA.  then theres AGI.  AGI has a direct result in avoidance.  though not big. but its there. 10 points isnt going to show in a parse but 10 hp or 10 ac isnt going to show either... 10 hp would matter in theory as opposed to agi's concrete and measurable impact? fascinating.<br>
<br>
So thats STR, STA, AGI. then theres dex.  dex increases proc rates but thats not while i recommend it to a newbie.  you see dex has a discernable effect on skill gain.  I was reading a thread once bout rogues and high level defense skill caps.  the moderator of safehouse through out a bad equation. i knew cause by defense was 4 points higher then the supposed cap at level 58.  its funny the same people that push ac/hp gear with str/sta stats end up with less AC then me in stat gear cause their D wont rise.  i end up with more stats and more ac via maxed D which just discredits the whole theory that str owns all at the start.  which gives rise to the subtle influence of dex.   levels are useless without skill rises in the early part of this game.  a horrid dex will be an endless source of slowness.  funny part is while you wont notice 15 points of str you do notice 15 points of dex in skill rises...<br>
<br>
so thats str,sta, agi,dex<br>
<br>
now granted meleers dont have much use for int and wis but in choosing a race the dumb ones are going to show it in skill rises.  even combat skills. dont ask me why i have the 112 int but along with the dex i believe it was a contributing factor in the maxed d and the one fight skill maxes that i saw in my whole career.<br>
<br>
Now i dont suppose your going to dare tell a caster that wis and int dont matter.  that would be amusing.  though even casters eye that sta for hp.  <br>
<br>
Then there is chr.  my god man talk to your friend thats a bard.  you do know they carry around an entire bag of chr gear dont you?  all cause chr doesnt matter? right.<br>
<br>
<br>
then there is ac.  the myth that ac doesnt matter came from its diminishing returns.  which is true. but the point of dimishing returns got pushed up in each expansion.  ac matters for most of us that dont have insane ac.<br>
<br>
then there is hp. it matters in bulk.<br>
<br>
so there it is and oddly it all matters.   i mean you cant devote 5 pieces to hp and compare that to devoting 1 piece to str.  if your pushing 5 pieces at hp then compare it to pushing 5 pieces to str.  then tell me that avatar is useless cause thats what im giving up in str.<br>
<br>
<br>
then there is the issue of what to twink with.  i ca double my characters hp true and strong. but you can also quadrouple their attack ratings.   true and strong.<br>
<br>
the odd part of the whole stat/ac/hp thing is that for a rogue which is all i know its hard to f**k it up. everyone has their favorites but @#%$ shows.<br>
<br>
personally for my moderate gear i rate resist above hp.  now resist have dimishing returns i understand but im talking under a 100 i rate it higher then hp.    its odd how many newbies overlook 10 magic resistance when it sooo clearly matters.  <br>
<br>
you really got to stay away from rather 1 dimensional viewpoints like hp is best and stay focused on which stat your working / how fatal it is if your working it suddenly (this is why i tend towards resist).  sometimes its attack sometimes its hp sometimes its resist.  its all bout whats going on.  <br>
<br>
and so i conclude that the whole stat dont matter thing is such an eq legend.<br>
